      • drive

        public int drive​(int kilometres)
        A method for driving a small car. A small car consumes fuel at the same rate for the duration of a journey.
        Parameters:
        kilometres - The distance (in kilometres) that a car is to drive.
        Returns:
        An integer representing the amount of fuel (in litres) that a car has consumed whilst driving. If the car is not driven then 0 is returned.
